parameters:
Mage Relm: Huh, what is this... something is... invading the
space...?

Bard: I made sure your friends weren't involved. Well, I
don't think it matters to you anymore.

Mage Relm: The space is warping... this is... not human...
I... I...
Would you like to skip the adult scene?

Would you like to retry the battle? If you choose No, it
will result in a game over.
Thief Nora: Well, it's that creepy place again!
Bard: Oh, I didn't expect you to come.

Priestess Sophia: I didn't want to come, but Clea-chan
insisted so much.

Mage Relm: A space like a barrier... It's completely
different from the concept of magic after all.

Bard: I didn't really mind going anywhere, but it's a bit
troublesome if people see us.

Bard: This place requires a considerable amount of power to
maintain its isolation from reality.

Bard: So, I think my power is... hmm, enough to casually
kill a dragon.
Clea: But it's still an overwhelming wonder.

Mage Relm: Just to confirm... we're talking about the dragon
we fought, right?

Bard: Haha, I wonder if I can casually kill about 10 fully
grown dragons?

Thief Nora: L-Let's run! The captain also said to choose our
opponents!

Bard: Of course, I won't go all out, and I won't do anything
that would take your lives.

Bard: I'm not forcing anyone to fight, but I feel like I can
remember things better if I fight a little.
Clea: I'm not sure if we can have a memorable battle.
Clea: Allow me to take on the challenge.
Bard: Thank you, let me know when you're ready.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置
Hero: Well then, shall we begin?
Bard: You all are really amazing.

Bard: If we're in such a sorry state, the goddesses might
get angry with us.

Bard: This time, I'll present you with a poetry collection I
made.

Bard: If you ever feel like fighting again, come and visit
me.
Bard: Too bad. If you feel like it, come and visit me again.
Bard: I can't believe I lost, I'm surprised.
Clea: I managed to somehow get by with going easy on you...

Bard: I want to give you something... Oh, I know! I'll give
you a collection of poems I wrote as a gift!
Bard: Is there anything else I can give you...?
Mage Relm: Please tell me about when you became a hero!
Priestess Sophia: I would also like to hear about it.
Thief Nora: But, like me, her memories...

Bard: Since it's not like I have amnesia or anything, if
it's okay to be a bit vague, I'll sing the story of the hero
for you.
キャラクターエピソード:吟遊詩人

Bard: I think this is about it. With this, the story of the
hero comes to an end.

Bard: I think it was hard to imagine the passage of time
because I only talked about the impressive parts.
Clea: Thank you very much for sharing such a valuable story.

Clea: However, there's just something that I really need to
ask...

Bard: Ahaha, I guess I can't cure my tone-deafness. I've
been practicing all this time, though.

Bard: If you ever feel like testing your skills, just let me
know.
Bard: I'll prepare a new collection of poems.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置
